<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="579" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,682,1103]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,682,707]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
(1) Thorax with pronotal width greater than transocular width of head; (2) *male pygofer with thin elongate setae on anteroventral portion; (3) *subgenital plate with thin elongate intercalary setae between macrosetae; (4) connective T-shaped; (5) style with apex truncate, with distinct outer anteapical lobe *bearing single elongate seta; (6) aedeagus with one or two pairs of apical processes; (7) paraphyses present; and (8) female sternite VII with dentiform projection at middle of posterior margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="579" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,682,1103]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,862,887]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">Remarks.</emphasis>
Features marked with an asterisk (*) were herein added to the diagnosis and are present in all species. The following features were removed from the diagnosis: (1) “aedeagus with ventral margin concave,” which does not apply to 
<taxonomicName authority="Cavichioli &amp; Rendón-Mera &amp; Domahovski &amp; Mejdalani, 2018" authorityName="Cavichioli &amp; Rendón-Mera &amp; Domahovski &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[422,490,935,958]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Geitogonalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piei" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[422,490,935,958]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">G. piei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[501,590,934,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[501,590,934,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cavichioli &amp; Rendón-Mera &amp; Domahovski &amp; Mejdalani, 2018" authorityName="Cavichioli &amp; Rendón-Mera &amp; Domahovski &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[644,786,935,958]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Geitogonalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetracorni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[644,786,935,958]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">G. tetracorni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[792,881,934,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[792,881,934,959]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
(ventral margin convex in the former and straight in the latter); and (2) “aedeagus with a pair of apical processes directed dorsally,” which is not observed in 
<taxonomicName authority="Cavichioli &amp; Rendón-Mera &amp; Domahovski &amp; Mejdalani, 2018" authorityName="Cavichioli &amp; Rendón-Mera &amp; Domahovski &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Geitogonalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buccina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">G. buccina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[252,346,1006,1031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[252,346,1006,1031]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
whose pair of apical processes are directed anterad and curved ventrally. In all species the aedeagus has at least one pair of apical processes (
<taxonomicName authority="Cavichioli &amp; Rendón-Mera &amp; Domahovski &amp; Mejdalani, 2018" authorityName="Cavichioli &amp; Rendón-Mera &amp; Domahovski &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[733,877,1043,1066]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Geitogonalia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tetracorni" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[733,877,1043,1066]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">G. tetracorni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[886,978,1042,1067]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[886,978,1042,1067]" pageId="1" pageNumber="579" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has two pairs, one dorsally and another ventrally).
</paragraph>
